I"K<p>I am an <em>Environmental Data Scientist</em> at the British Antarctic Survey (<a href="http://www.bas.ac.uk">BAS</a>) and <em>Head of the</em> <a href="http://www.bas.ac.uk/ai"><em>BAS AI Lab</em></a>. I am also a <em>Senior Research Fellow</em> at the <a href="https://www.turing.ac.uk/">Alan Turing Institute</a>, and a <em>Co-Director</em> of the UKRI Centre for Doctoral Training (CDT) in the <em>Application of AI for the study of Environmental Risks</em> (<a href="https://ai4er-cdt.esc.cam.ac.uk/"><em>AI4ER</em></a>) at the University of Cambridge.</p>

<p>My research focuses on the application of <strong>AI and machine learning</strong> to identify and understand the mechanisms that drive <strong>high-impact climate events</strong> in order to reduce uncertainties in future environemntal change and help inform <strong>environmental policy</strong>.</p>

